RevolutionPlus Property, the official real estate partner of the NFF  has pledged a handsome N1m per goal as the Super Eagles  continue their campaign on Sunday in the knock-out stages of the on-going  Africa Cup of Nations(AFCON) Cameroon 2021. The company’s Group Managing Director/ CEO Bamidele Onalaja  said the gesture is aimed at giving the team a boost in its quest to win the continental cup for Nigeria and make Nigerians proud again.  “Now that the Super Eagles have qualified for the knockout stages of AFCON, RevolutionPlus Group will pay N1m for each goal scored by the team at every knockout stages of the competition, “ Onalaja said, adding: “ this is in appreciation of the team’s performance in the competition so far and the need to encourage the players to do more for fatherland.   Iheanacho: Eagles have new identity     Buhari lauds winning Super Eagles     G/Bissau 0-2 Nigeria: Exciting Super Eagles tame Wild Dog   Onalaja also reaffirmed his earlier pledge of N4m to the team during the World Cup qualifiers and urged them to bring AFCON glory to Nigeria once again. - Advertisement - Meanwhile, RevolutionPlus Property will be  giving  free lands in choice locations within its estates to the Super Eagles if the team wins the on-going AFCON trophy. According to Bamidele Onalaja, the company’s Group Managing Director/ CEO, the lands will be available in choice locations in  Lagos, Abuja FCT, Nasarawa,  Abeokuta, Shimawa and Mowe in Ogun State, Ibadan, the capital of Oyo State and Port Harcourt Rivers State.